						               													<description>Presented at Lucca Games 2010 by Editrice Giochi.&amp;#10;Tank Attack! Card Game is for 2-6 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Content:&amp;#10;A fleet of tanks and flags are useful to keep track of the points scored by the players during the game. The big ones 5 points, small one 1 and the flags 10 points.&amp;#10;A tin box to contain tanks and flags.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The United States have been invaded by an unknown enemy. The players must free the inhabitants of the 50 American States, one at a time, playing the cards in their hands strategically.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;110 cards: 50 &amp;quot;States&amp;quot; and 60 &amp;quot;Tanks&amp;quot;. 50 States represents 50 States of US and each card indicates the name of the state, its position within the USA, the flag, the geographic boundaries and a value which is proportional to the actual number of inhabitants of each states.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play.&amp;#10;The first &amp;quot;states&amp;quot; card is turned and represents the objective of the current hand.&amp;#10;Each player choses one card among his 5 &amp;quot;Tanks&amp;quot; cards, when all players have chosen their cards, the cards played are revealed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who plays the card with greater value wins the State.&amp;#10;The value of the state represents the score obtained and who won this card take relative number of tanks and flags and placing in front of him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all the States are freed or when one of the players reaches a pre-set score that varies according to number of players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Tanks cards are discarded and replaced by other cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Integrated Risk: a new complete set of fleet of a new color give option to add a new player to Risk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
